---
By: Gautama Buddha
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 201
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Good
---
Let no man think lightly of good, saying in his heart, “it will not benefit
me.” As by the falling of raindrops a jar of water is filled, so the wise
man becomes full of good, even though he collects it little by little.
